= ⬡ QUARTER I GATHERING — The Grey Wolf

*Theme:* First mineral preparations shared; the threshold experience of crossing into mineral work.

#hm-note[
  The threshold experience of moving from vegetable and water work into mineral
  work is qualitatively different for every student. Some find it exciting;
  some find it sobering; some find it unexpectedly difficult in ways they did not
  anticipate. All of these are appropriate. The gathering is a space for honest
  sharing — not performance of enthusiasm.
]

*Students share:*
- Their Vinegar of Antimony preparation: appearance, properties, comparison
  with plant vinegar.
- Their first Via Humida mineral preparation: current state after two cycles.
- A reflection on what was most surprising or difficult about crossing into
  mineral work.
- One reading from GCH III that has most illuminated or puzzled them.

